article.description: Algevon Eichelber scored 17 points and Deante Johnson scored 15 and Cleveland State beat Detroit Mercy 67-66 in overtime on Saturday.
article.headline: Patton's late 3 in OT sends Cleveland St. past Detroit Mercy
article.linkText: Patton's late 3 in OT sends Cleveland St. past Detroit Mercy
article.story: DETROIT -- Algevon Eichelberger scored 17 points and Deante Johnson scored 15 and Cleveland State beat Detroit Mercy 67-66 in overtime on Saturday. Torrey Patton's 3-pointer broke a tie at 63 with 34 seconds left in the extra session and the Vikings (10-17, 6-8 Horizon League) held onwin. Dwayne Rose Jr. hit a 3-pointer with 95 seconds at the end of regulation to put Detroit Merchy up 59-58. Eichelberger made 1 of 2 fouls shots to tie it with 1:17 left and neither team scored again to force overtime. Patton finished with 13 points, Kasheem Thomas 11 and Jeremy Sanchez 10. Cleveland State finished 27-of-65 shooting (41.5%). The Vikings got the win despite just a 4 of 15 effort from 3-point range and 10 missed free throws. Marquis Moore led Detroit Mercy with 20 points and Antoine Davis added 17. --- More AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25
